Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Trapezoid-shaped mummy breast cover, rounded at the bottom. From top to bottom: a wesekh-collar with two falcon heads. In the curve, two udjat-eyes each placed upon a neb sign (''lord, all, every''). A kneeling goddess (Nut), wearing the solar disc and with out-stretched wings, holding a Maat feather in each hand. The four sons of Horus appear on either side of the door upon which the goddess is kneeling. Hepi and Qebehsenuf on the left, Amset and Duamutef on the right. Two erect cobras, facing the door. Compare with L 1375. Brick-red background and contours and details in black.
